definitions.definition: The fact of being organic ; organicity .
Something with many separate interdependent parts, seen as being like a living thing; an organic system .
A discrete and complete living thing, such as animal , plant , fungus or microorganism .

main_definition: ( obsolete , rare ) The fact of being organic ; organicity . [18th–19th c.]
secondary_definitions: Something with many separate interdependent parts, seen as being like a living thing; an organic system . [from 18th c.]
( biology ) A discrete and complete living thing, such as animal , plant , fungus or microorganism . [from 19th c.]
